the Event of Hurrah are also buried in Baqi. After the tragedy of Karbala and the martyrdom of Imam Hussain (a) and his companions, the people of Madina revolted against the Umayyad rule and dethroned the governor of Madina. Yazid sent a large army to suppress the revolt and his army plundered Madina for 3 days continuously, killing people and looting their property and the honor of their women. Thousands perished in this attack including 80 companions of the Holy Prophet (s) and 700 children of the Ansaar and Mohajereen (Helpers and Emigrants). This incident is famous as \"Hurrah\". The martyrs of this attack are buried in Baqi.", "GujaratiDescription": null, "RUrduDescription": "Waqeya Hurrah ke shaheed bhi is Baqi mein dafn hai. Karbala ke waaqye aur Imam Husain (a) aur unke saathiyo’n ki shahadat ke baad, Madine ke logo’n ne bani ummayya ke khilaaf awaaz uthaayi aur Madine ke governer ko wahan se hata diya. Is par Yazid ne ek bada lashkar Madine ki taraf rawaana kiya jo Madine waalo’n ka 3 din tak qatle aam, loot aur aurto’n ki izzat ko pa-maal kiya. Hazaaro’n ki tadaad mein log is hamle mein shaheed huwe jis mein Rasool (s) ke 80 sahaabi bhi thay aur 700 Ansaar aur Mohajereen ke bachche bhi thay. Yeh waqya “Hurrah” ke naam se mashhoor hai. Is waqye mein jo shaheed huwe, woh bhi is Baqi mein dafn hai.", "UrduDescription": null, "English": null, "Gujarati": null, "RGujarati": null, "RUrdu": null, "Urdu": null, "RArabic": null, "ArabicText1": null, "ArabicGreenSign1": null, "ArabicRedSign1": null, "ArabicBlueSign1": null, "ArabicText2": null, "ArabicGreenSign2": null, "ArabicRedSign2": null, "ArabicBlueSign2": null, "ArabicText3": null, "ArabicGreenSign3": null, "ArabicRedSign3": null, "ArabicBlueSign3": null, "ArabicText4": null, "ArabicGreenSign4": null, "ArabicRedSign4": null, "ArabicBlueSign4": null, "ArabicText5": null, "ArabicGreenSign5": null, "ArabicRedSign5": null, "ArabicBlueSign5": null, "ArabicText6": null, "ArabicGreenSign6": null, "ArabicRedSign6": n